communications.subject: Georgia Open Records Act Request: GA CVR Data Request (2022, 2024) (Lumpkin County Election And Registration Office)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Georgia Open Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

Cast vote record (CVR) data for the following elections:
1. 2022 Nov Midterm Election
2. 2024 Nov General Election

Specifically, I’m looking for the full anonymized record of votes cast each election generated by the Dominion voting system. Forsyth County has an example of these records posted for the 2024 General Election under the name “Cast Vote Records (CVR) Report” at this link: https://www.forsythco.com/Departments-Offices/Voter-Registrations-Elections/Election-Results. Please let me know if you need any further clarification on the type of data that I am requesting.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 3 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Aleksandra Conevska

communications.subject: New York Freedom of Information Law Request: Evergreen Solutions (Niagara County Community College)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the New York Freedom of Information Law, I hereby request the following records:

To Whom It May Concern:


Subject: Request for Public Records - 

Greetings,

I hope this email finds you well. We at Evergreen Solutions, LLC, are conducting a compensation study on behalf of our client and I am writing to make a formal open records request. We are requesting an electronic copy of your staff and faculty (if applicable) database as well as relevant documents such as job descriptions, collective bargaining agreements, and pay plans. I am able to send survey templates to assist with the data collection; however, we will accept data in the manner most convenient for you.

Staff Census Information requested:

Job Titles
Classification Title
Pay Grades
Pay Ranges (Minimum and Maximum)
Actual Salaries
Full-Time Equivalent (FTE) Status
Staff Handbook

I also kindly request answers to the following questions related to the compensation study:

How are salaries adjusted for your organization (e.g., COLA, Longevity, performance, etc.)?
What is your current turnover rate?
What is your current average tenure for an employee?
Date your current compensation plan was implemented.
Date of the last salary adjustment?
How frequently are job descriptions updated?

For the faculty database, I am requesting the following information:

Faculty Census:
Rank (if applicable)
Classification Title (if faculty holds other positions other than teaching such as Dean, Chair, Coordinators,etc)
Highest Degree Held
Pay Grade
Pay Ranges (Min& Max)
Current Step (if on a step plan)
Contract Length (in days and/or months)
Annual Base Salary with no additives
Annual Salary with any additives
Discipline (Not to be confused with department, the distinct/specific subject the faculty member teaches; Ex: Microbiology)
Department
CIP Code (if available - by individual incumbent)

Additionally, copies of the following documents, if available:

Copy of all faculty pay plans
Employee Benefit Information (Holidays Off, Health Insurance, Etc)
Salary Adjustment Policy (Longevity, performance, COLA, etc)
Any Collective Bargaining Agreements
Current Turnover Rate
Current Average Tenure
Date that your current pay plan was implemented
Date of your last salary adjustment to pay plan
How frequently are your job descriptions updated
Do you have a planned salary adjustment to your compensation structures for the next fiscal year? If so, by what amount?
Please list/attach and supplements/additives that faculty are compensated for duties outside of instruction
Faculty Handbooks
Adjunct Rates/Pay Plan
Overload Rates
Rates for compensation for faculty leadership- Deans, Coordinators, Department Chairs
Do you compensate faculty differently based on area of discipline? If yes, please provide details.
Do you have any form of additional compensation for Large Class Size? If yes, please provide details.
Do you have an education incentive at your institution? If yes, please provide details.

I understand that public records requests may involve administrative processes and associated fees, as allowed by law. Please inform me of any fees and the estimated timeframe for fulfilling this request. If any portion of this request is denied, please provide a written explanation for the denial, citing the specific legal grounds for the refusal.

Please consider this email as a formal request for public records under the applicable open records laws. If there are any questions or additional details needed to process this request, please do not hesitate to contact me.

I look forward to your prompt attention to this matter and the timely provision of the requested information. Your cooperation in ensuring transparency and access to public records is greatly appreciated.

Do you agree to the redaction of information that is subject to mandatory exceptions, provided such redactions are clearly labeled on information you receive?: Yes
Do you agree to the redaction of information that is subject to discretionary exceptions, provided such redactions are clearly labeled on information you receive? Yes

Email: alisia@consultevergreen.com

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Alisia Rios

communications.communication:
Good Afternoon,
I have the answers to your questions. 

1. Is the salary structure reflective of all the employees? Meaning these are all the employees who work at the institution? Wanted to ask since there were only 48 positions.

Answer: The information provided was for Administrators. All other employees are in a CBA. 

- Is there anything to indicate the actual salary and their FTE? 

Answer: That is the actual salary as FTE. 

2. Are these "groups" official pay grades for the employees?

Answer: There are ranges based on benchmarking for recruitment and retention. 

3. Are there job descriptions for these staff positions?

Answer: Only have job descriptions for Administrators. Clerical (ESPA), Security (ESPA) Maintenance and Operations (TSPA) is civil service: https://www.niagaracounty.gov/employment/job_specs_for_civil_service_positions.php. Rates are also in the CBA’s that were already provided, and faculty is in the handbook which is attached as well. 


Please let me know if there is anything else needed.

Thank You,
Kristin Leszkowicz

communications.communication:

I was not able to submit my responses to this request via the link in the email, therefore, I am including them in this email in red with an attachment. Please let me know that you have received this response.


1. Is the salary structure reflective of all the employees? Meaning these are all the employees who work at the institution? Wanted to ask since there were only 48 positions. The salary structure is for Administrators (non-union)  only as listed. The other ranges are part of the CBA which was provided.

Answer: The information provided was for Administrators. All other employees are in a CBA.

Follow Up: Is it possible to get a copy of that? The current one does not show non-faculty positions with the salaries Attached

2. Is there anything to indicate the actual salary and their FTE?

Answer: That is the actual salary as FTE.
Follow-up: When I ask about "FTE" I mean if these positions are full time or part time. Also, by actual salary, I mean the actual amount the employee earns, and not potential like the ranges indicate. Full-time which equates to a minimum of 35 hours per week.

Thank You,

Kristin Leszkowicz

SUNY Niagara

Thanks for your response! My name is Rebecca Burns and my colleague Julia Rock and I are reporters at The Lever, a national investigative outlet. I am making this request as part of ongoing reporting into water issues in the American West. This request is not being made for commercial purposes. 

My mailing address is 4521 N Central Park Ave. 3W, Chicago IL 60625. My phone number is 781-962-8816. Please feel free to give me a call if it's helpful to discuss any portion of this request. 

Thank you!

Dear Mr. Scroggins and Ms. Olsen,

Thanks for the update. Can you provide any additional info regarding the source of delays on this request, or the estimated delivery date? Please feel free to give me a call at 781-962-8816 if it'd be helpful to discuss the scope of the materials we're requesting.

communications.subject: RE: New Mexico Inspection of Public Records Act Request: Water Asset Management funds correspondence
communications.communication:
Dear Ms. Rock,

I am responding to your email yesterday requesting any additional info regarding the source of delays on this request. Please be assured that we make every effort to respond promptly to every request. However, we must also ensure that we are diligent and accurate in our reply. Thus, when obtained, all documents and emails must be reviewed. Additionally, we must rely on the state agency that controls the entire state email system to identify and provide the emails requested. As you can imagine, the process takes time.

As to an estimated response date, in our letter of August 1, 2023, we noted that we intend to respond by September 6, 2023.

Thank you for your patience and please feel free to contact me if you have further questions.

Respectfully,

[cid:image001.png@01D9C623.0D3F7D80]

communications.subject: ATTORNEY CLIENT PRIVILEGED - RE: [EXTERNAL] RE: New Mexico Inspection of Public Records Act Request: Water Asset Management funds correspondence
communications.communication:
Dear Ms. Rock and Ms. Burns,

Thank you for your inquiry and please accept our apologies for the delay.

As Mr. Scroggins noted in his August 3, 2023 email regarding our projected response, we always try to be prompt.  But as you might guess, the request references a large number of records.  As he said, we must thoroughly review all records to identify and obtain the responsive documents from both external and internal sources.  It is a complex and time-consuming process.

I am confident that we will have documents ready to provide on or before the December 6th, 2023, date noted in our recent communication.

Thank you for your continued patience!
Regards,
Renee



[cid:image002.png@01DA121F.C2136CB0]

As discussed in our letter of December 6, 2023, we are providing the records we currently have available in response to your June 16, 2023, request.  They are located at the website below:

MuckRock - Julia Rock<https://nmgov-my.sharepoint.com/:f:/r/personal/renee_garcia_erb_nm_gov/Documents/MuckRock%20-%20Julia%20Rock?csf=1&web=1&e=4gwfSH>

As also discussed, we will require additional time to provide the remainder of the records.  We plan to provide additional documents on or before February 1, 2024.  Thank you again for your continued patience regarding this matter.
Regards,
Renee

communications.subject: Illinois Freedom of Information Act. Request: Shooting Targets (Chicago Police Department)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Illinois Freedom of Information Act., I hereby request the following records:

I am requesting records related to the purchase and use of targets used for marksmanship training:

Targets are defined as paper and metal targets used by the department for shooting lethal and nonlethal weapons (40mm foam rounds, tasers, etc). They can be stationary or moving. 

Purchase and invoice records for targets
Scans, photos, website links, and any record that shows what the targets look like

Search 2018 to today’s date.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Joey Scott

communications.subject: Nevada Public Records Act Request: Nevada SEA response
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Nevada Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

All documentation submitted to the U.S. Department of Education's Student Privacy Policy Office in response to the office's March 28, 2025, request for records such as "'reports, information on policies and procedures, annual notifications, training materials or other information necessary' to provide assurance that the SEA and their respective LEAs are complying with the provisions of FERPA and PPRA".

I have attached a copy of the SPPO's request letter for reference. The relevant section is found on the last page, under "Assurance of Compliance". The SPPO requested the documentation be submitted no later than April 30, 2025. If the Nevada Department of Education sent communications to the SPPO requesting an extension or declining to submit the documentation, I request a copy of said communications.

I also request that, if appropriate, fees be waived as I believe this request is in the public interest. The requested documents will be made available to the general public free of charge as part of the public information service at MuckRock.com, processed by a representative of the news media/press and is made in the process of news gathering and not for commercial usage.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Ileana Garnand

communications.subject: Texas Public Information Act Request: Stephen Presnull Offense Report (McLennan County Sheriff)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Texas Public Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

Dear Personnel Division,

I hope this message finds you well.

I am writing to request any police reports, calls for service, and documented reprimands involving Stephen Presnull, a former employee of your organization. This information is intended for public use and will be made available to the public.

Please note that Stephen Presnull was a public servant, and the requested records are not for personal use but for transparency and public knowledge.

Thank you for your attention to this request. I look forward to your prompt response.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Stephen

Your request has been received and is being processed. Your request was received in this office on 3/26/2025 and given the reference number R000905-032625 for tracking purposes. 
 Records Requested: To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Texas Public Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

Dear Personnel Division,

I hope this message finds you well.

I am writing to request any police reports, calls for service, and documented reprimands involving Stephen Presnull, a former employee of your organization. This information is intended for public use and will be made available to the public.

Please note that Stephen Presnull was a public servant, and the requested records are not for personal use but for transparency and public knowledge.

Thank you for your attention to this request. I look forward to your prompt response.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Sincerely,

Stephen

You can monitor the progress of your request at the link below and you'll receive an email when your request has been completed. 
 
McLennan County Sheriff's Office

communications.subject: Freedom of Information Act Request: Cancellation of Ryan Holiday speech
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

1. Any communications, on or after April 1, 2025, concerning the planned appearance by Ryan Holiday on April 14, 2025, as reported in this New York Times piece: https://www.nytimes.com/2025/04/19/opinion/naval-academy-speech-censorship.html.

2. Any communications, on or after April 1, 2025, concerning the cancellation, postponement, or rescheduling of Ryan Holiday's April 14, 2025 appearance.

"Communications" means and includes emails, text messages, social media messages, letters, memoranda, calendar entries, chats, or any form of one-to-one or one-to-many communication.

Please note that this request seeks public records wherever they may be found, including on devices or networks owned or operated by private parties. For example, if an employee uses a personal cell phone or social media account to conduct public business, records created, maintained, or held on the phone or account are public records subject to this request.

REQUEST FOR EXPEDITED PROCESSING:

I request that this request be expedited under 32 CFR § 286.8(e)(1)(i)(B) for the following reasons:

1. I certify the following to be true and correct: My organization is primarily engaged in disseminating information. The Foundation for Individual Rights and Expression (FIRE) maintains a news website at https://thefire.org/news, through which its staff members regularly publish news stories and editorial content concerning the activities of governments, government officials, and other persons or organizations of public concern. I am a staff member of FIRE. I frequently write about matters involving the First Amendment and press freedom, including on FIRE's website. See, e.g., https://www.thefire.org/news-archive?author=303. A substantial component of my duties as a staff member of FIRE is to obtain information through public records requests, including through the Freedom of Information Act, which I or my colleagues then share through FIRE's website and social media channels. I also publish news and other information of public concern via "X" (https://x.com/adamsteinbaugh) and "Bluesky" (https://bsky.app/profile/adamsteinbaugh.bsky.social).

2. The requested information concerns an actual or alleged government activity, namely the removal of books from a library due to their viewpoints or content and the cancellation of a speech on the basis that discussion of those books (or their removal) might violate an order of the President of the United States.

3. The requested information extends beyond the public's right to know about government activity generally and instead has a particular value that would be lost if not processed on an expedited basis. The information pertains to breaking news story of public interest. That issue has attracted media coverage, including the Associated Press report identified above. The information has value that would be lost if not processed on an expedited basis.

REQUEST FOR A FEE WAIVER OR REDUCED FEES:

I request, under 32 CFR § 286.12(l), a waiver or reduction of fees for the following reasons:

1. Disclosure of the requested information is in the public interest because its disclosure would shed light on the operations or activities of the government. The requested information pertains specifically to the cancellation of a speech based on its contents or viewpoint.

2. Disclosure of the requested information would be likely to contribute significantly to public understanding of those operations or activities. Disclosure of the requested information would meaningfully inform the public about the Department's activities and operations. That information is not in the public domain and relates to a decision that has received attention from a prominent newspaper.

3. Disclosure of the requested information will contribute to the understanding of a reasonably broad audience of persons interested in the subject, as opposed to the individual understanding of the requester. The requestor is a licensed attorney who practices First Amendment law, including its application to members of the press. As such, the requestor will be able to effectively convey information to the public. Further, the requestor is a representative of the news media. The requestor and his employer, the Foundation for Individual Rights and Expression, gather information of potential interest to a segment of the public, turns that information into distinct works (including through its news website, located at https://thefire.org/news), and distributes that information to the public. The information requested here relates to information that is about current events or that would be of current interest to the public. The requestor's past publication record (in addition to FIRE's articles available at https://thefire.org/news) is available at https://www.thefire.org/news-archive?author=303.

4. The requested information is not primarily in the commercial interest of the requester. The requestor works for a nonprofit organization and the records are not sought for a commercial purpose.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Adam Steinbaugh

communications.subject: FOIA/PA Request 2025-NavyFOIA-006581
communications.communication:
Dear Mr. Steinbaugh,

Please find the final disposition letter and responsive records for the
subject Freedom of Information Act request attached.

If you have any questions or need any further assistance, please contact me
at foia@usna.edu or (410)-293-1550.  You may also contact the DON FOIA
Public Liaison, Christopher Julka, at *christopher.a.julka.civ@us.navy.mil
<christopher.a.julka.civ@us.navy.mil>*, (703)-697-0031.  In addition, the
Office of Government Information Services (OGIS) provides a voluntary
mediation process for resolving disputes between persons making FOIA
requests and the Department of the Navy (DON).  For more information, go to
https://www.archives.gov/ogis/about-ogis/contact-information

If at any point you wish to make an appeal, your appeal options are below
and will also be explained in greater detail in your final disposition
letter when received.  The two main ways to file an appeal are by mail or
through the Internet.

1. By mail. Address your appeal to:

The Judge Advocate General (Code 14)
1322 Patterson Avenue SE, Suite 3000
 Washington Navy Yard, DC 20374-5066

2. Through the Internet. Use the public portal of SecureRelease (the
Department of the Navy's FOIA processing system). Go to
https://www.securerelease.us.  Click "Login/Create Account" (in the
top-right corner) and enter the information in the boxes that appear to
create an account. Once that is done, you will be able to file an appeal
for any request created through the SecureRelease portal by clicking the
Create Appeal button in the top-right corner of the Request page.

3. By email. The Judge Advocate General (Code 14) may be reached at
Navy-OJAG-C14-FOIA-PA-ADMINAPPEALS@us.navy.mil.

To appeal a request that was not submitted through the SecureRelease
portal, create a SecureRelease portal account, then use the Create Request
button on the SecureRelease portal homepage to create a FOIA request. In
the Request Description field for that FOIA request, indicate that this is
an appeal and make reference to the tracking number you have received for
the request you wish to appeal.

Sincerely,



*  Shannon C. Campbell*
  U.S. Naval Academy
  USNA FOIA/PA Coordinator
  mailto:foia@usna.edu <foia@usna.edu>
  (o) 410-293-1550  (f) 410-293-0005

communications.subject: New York Freedom of Information Law Request: Evergreen Solutions (West Genesee Central School District Office)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the New York Freedom of Information Law, I hereby request the following records:

To Whom It May Concern:


Subject: Request for Public Records - 

Greetings,

I hope this email finds you well. We at Evergreen Solutions, LLC, are conducting a compensation study on behalf of our client and I am writing to make a formal open records request. We are requesting an electronic copy of your staff and faculty (if applicable) database as well as relevant documents such as job descriptions, collective bargaining agreements, and pay plans. I am able to send survey templates to assist with the data collection; however, we will accept data in the manner most convenient for you.

Staff Census Information requested:

Job Titles
Classification Title
Pay Grades
Pay Ranges (Minimum and Maximum)
Actual Salaries
Full-Time Equivalent (FTE) Status
Staff Handbook

I also kindly request answers to the following questions related to the compensation study:

How are salaries adjusted for your organization (e.g., COLA, Longevity, performance, etc.)?
What is your current turnover rate?
What is your current average tenure for an employee?
Date your current compensation plan was implemented.
Date of the last salary adjustment?
How frequently are job descriptions updated?

For the faculty database, I am requesting the following information:

Faculty Census:
Rank (if applicable)
Classification Title (if faculty holds other positions other than teaching such as Dean, Chair, Coordinators,etc)
Highest Degree Held
Pay Grade
Pay Ranges (Min& Max)
Current Step (if on a step plan)
Contract Length (in days and/or months)
Annual Base Salary with no additives
Annual Salary with any additives
Discipline (Not to be confused with department, the distinct/specific subject the faculty member teaches; Ex: Microbiology)
Department
CIP Code (if available - by individual incumbent)

Additionally, copies of the following documents, if available:

Copy of all faculty pay plans
Employee Benefit Information (Holidays Off, Health Insurance, Etc)
Salary Adjustment Policy (Longevity, performance, COLA, etc)
Any Collective Bargaining Agreements
Current Turnover Rate
Current Average Tenure
Date that your current pay plan was implemented
Date of your last salary adjustment to pay plan
How frequently are your job descriptions updated
Do you have a planned salary adjustment to your compensation structures for the next fiscal year? If so, by what amount?
Please list/attach and supplements/additives that faculty are compensated for duties outside of instruction
Faculty Handbooks
Adjunct Rates/Pay Plan
Overload Rates
Rates for compensation for faculty leadership- Deans, Coordinators, Department Chairs
Do you compensate faculty differently based on area of discipline? If yes, please provide details.
Do you have any form of additional compensation for Large Class Size? If yes, please provide details.
Do you have an education incentive at your institution? If yes, please provide details.

I understand that public records requests may involve administrative processes and associated fees, as allowed by law. Please inform me of any fees and the estimated timeframe for fulfilling this request. If any portion of this request is denied, please provide a written explanation for the denial, citing the specific legal grounds for the refusal.

Please consider this email as a formal request for public records under the applicable open records laws. If there are any questions or additional details needed to process this request, please do not hesitate to contact me.

I look forward to your prompt attention to this matter and the timely provision of the requested information. Your cooperation in ensuring transparency and access to public records is greatly appreciated.

Do you agree to the redaction of information that is subject to mandatory exceptions, provided such redactions are clearly labeled on information you receive?: Yes
Do you agree to the redaction of information that is subject to discretionary exceptions, provided such redactions are clearly labeled on information you receive? Yes

Email: alisia@consultevergreen.com

title: Request for Correctional Mental Health Staff Directory and Contact Information (Department of Corrections)

communications.subject: Minnesota Government Data Practices Act Request: Request for Correctional Mental Health Staff Directory and Contact Information (Department of Corrections)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Minnesota Government Data Practices Act, I hereby request the following records:

I am requesting a list of currently employed mental health professionals within your state's Department of Corrections or its subsidiary agencies, as well as their contact information.

Specifically, I am requesting:

- Full names
- Job titles
- Assigned correctional facility
- Government-issued email addresses
- Government-issued phone numbers (direct desk numbers if available, otherwise department phone numbers with or without extensions)
- Department/division (e.g. Behavioral Health, Mental Health Services)

This request applies to the following roles: rehabilitative program coordinators, licensed psychologists, psychiatrists, clinical social workers, and other licensed mental health professionals serving incarcerated populations in state-operated facilities.

If available, I request this information be provided in a machine-readable format such as CSV or Excel.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days.

Sincerely,

Andrew Ma

communications.subject: Government Records Access and Management Act Request: Utah DOC transgender policies
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Government Records Access and Management Act, I hereby request the following records:

All department policy and guidance documents regarding transgender inmates, including but not limited to gender-affirming medical care, housing and treatment by staff. I also request records of any proposed and/or enacted changes to said policies made on or after Nov. 6, 2024 until date of search, if such documents exist.

I request that, if appropriate, fees be waived as I believe this request is in the public interest. The requested documents will be made available to the general public free of charge as part of the public information service at MuckRock.com, processed by a representative of the news media/press and is made in the process of news gathering and not for commercial usage.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Ileana Garnand

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

Records mentioning, relating to, or generated as a result of investigation or inquiry of Ivan Frederick Boesky (March 6, 1937 - May 20, 2024). Proof of death is not required as his death was widely reported: https://www.nytimes.com/2024/05/20/business/ivan-f-boesky-dead.html

Please conduct a search of the Central Records System, including but not limited to the Electronic Surveillance (ELSUR) Indices, the Microphone Surveillance (MISUR) Indices, the Physical Surveillance (FISUR) Indices, and the Technical Surveillance (TESUR) Indices, for both main-file records and cross-reference records for all relevant names, individuals, agencies and companies. This is also to include any responsive records held in offsite locations, such as the Alexandria Records Center. Please include both investigatory and non-investigatory records in your search. If any potentially responsive records have been destroyed and/or transferred to NARA, then I request copies of the destruction or transfer slips as well as any other documentation relating to, mentioning or describing said transfer or destruction, to include but not be limited to confirmation that the Bureau has no other copies of said records. If previously released records are available, then I request a rolling release consisting of those records while additional records are located and processed for release.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Paul Galante

communications.subject: Freedom of Information Act Request: John Singlaub (FBI Records)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Under the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request all records related to Gen. John Kirk Singlaub. Singlaub was born July 10, 1921 in what is now Independence, California, USA. He died January 29, 2022.

ABOUT THE SUBJECT:

In May 1977, Singlaub (then the Army's third-ranking official on the Korean Peninsula) spoke out publicly against President Carter's decision to withdraw 32,000 ground troops from the Korean Peninsula.

Gen. Singlaub started the U.S. Council for World Freedom, an affiliate of the World Anti-Communist League. In addition, Gen. Singlaub was involved with the Western Goals Foundation, a private domestic intelligence group bankrolled by conservative Texas oil tycoon Nelson Bunker Hunt to gather information on leftist groups and their leaders. Gen. Singlaub’s chief function in what the Los Angeles Times called the business of “private-enterprise insurgency” was raising millions of dollars to supply arms to anti-communist paramilitaries in places such as Nicaragua, Angola, Afghanistan and Laos. He was also the chairman of the OSS Society, a group that seeks to preserve the legacy of the Office of Strategic Services, the precursor to the Central Intelligence Agency. In the early 1980s, as Congress began curtailing U.S. funding of efforts to overthrow leftist regimes in Nicaragua and elsewhere, Gen. Singlaub and his organizations remained an important conduit of materiel and financial assistance to right-wing paramilitaries, reportedly with the help of deep-pocketed conservatives and foreign governments.

SCOPE OF SEARCH: 

In addition to standard practices, please search the Electronic Surveillance (ELSUR) Indices, the Microphone Surveillance (MISUR) Indices, the Physical Surveillance (FISUR) Indices, and the Technical Surveillance (TESUR) Indices.

Please include a cross-reference search of the following things to see if they contain additional records related to Gen. Singlaub: U.S. COUNCIL FOR WORLD FREEDOM, WORLD ANTI-COMMUNIST LEAGUE, WESTERN GOALS FOUNDATION, OSS SOCIETY

REQUEST FOR FEE WAIVER:

Public Interest Factors

1. The subject of the request must concern identifiable operations or activities of the Federal Government. My request satisfies this factor because it seeks records created or maintained by the FBI.

2. The records must be likely to contribute to the understanding of the subject of the request. My request satisfies this factor because it seeks information that, to my knowledge, is not already in the public domain. Of course, without already knowing what records the Bureau has, I can't say for sure whether those records are already in the public domain or what the public would learn from them; however, because Gen. Singlaub has recently died, the Bureau may now be able to release records that were not previously available via the FOIA/PA.

3. The disclosure must contribute to the understanding of the public—meaning a reasonably broad audience of persons interested in the subject—as opposed to the individual understanding of the requester. My request satisfies this factor because Gen. Singlaub was a public figure. News obituaries for Gen. Singlaub appeared in the Washington Post and the New York Times, among other publications. Thus, a broad audience of persons will likely be interested in the records I seek. I will also make any records available online for free via muckrock.com, a FOIA-and-journalism site that lets people share the results of their FOIA requests and encourages journalism around them.

4. The public's understanding must be enhanced by the disclosure to a significant extent. My request likely satisfies this factor because Gen. Singlaub has recently died—meaning that the Bureau can now release responsive records that it could not have released before. Again, I cannot be 100% sure if factor is satisfied without already knowing what records the Bureau has. However, given Gen. Singlaub's status as a U.S. Army General, a public figure, and a private funder of right-wing paramilitaries, the Bureau should deem this factor satisfied.

Commercial Interest Factors

1. The existence and magnitude of a commercial interest: I have no commercial interest whatsoever in these records; I am just a curious American citizen with an interest in his government's surveillance of its critics. Thus, this factor cuts in favor of a fee waiver.

2. The primary interest in disclosure, i.e., whether disclosure is primarily in the commercial interest of the requester: I have zero commercial interest in disclosure, therefore the public interest outweighs my (nonexistent) private interest.

Conclusion

On balance, all of the Bureau's regulatory factors tilt decisively in favor of granting me a fee waiver. If you do decide to charge me fees, please notify me in advance if you anticipate that those fees will exceed $25.

Sincerely,

Nicholas Marritz

NOTE: Recent requests are entered into the FOIPA database in the order that they are received. Before you can check the status, you must have received correspondence assigning a FOIPA request number and the information transferred to the online database. Status information is updated weekly. If a request has been closed within the last six months the online database will display the following: The FOIPA number entered has been closed, and appropriate correspondence has been sent to the address on file.

Estimated Dates of Completion
Requests are processed in the order in which they are received through our multi-track processing system.  Requests are divided into two primary tracks--simple (under 50 pages of potentially responsive documents) and complex (over 50 pages of potentially responsive documents).  Complex requests are further divided into medium, large, and extra-large sub-tracks based upon request size.  Simple track requests typically require the least amount of time to process.  Currently, simple track cases average approximately 111 days from the date of receipt for processing.  Our complex requests in the medium processing track are currently averaging 895 days, large processing track are currently averaging approximately 1,929 days, and extra-large processing track are currently averaging 2,360 days for processing.

communications.subject: Freedom of Information Act Request: Chief FOIA officer's recent email (Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco, Firearms and Explosives)
communications.communication:
Dear Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco, Firearms and Explosives,

On behalf of myself and Fiat Fiendum, I hereby request the following records:

1. The one email in your chief FOIA officer's email inbox or equivalent which was received nearest and before October 19, 2024, midnight Eastern time, regardless of subject matter.
2. The one email in your chief FOIA officer's email spam folder or equivalent which was received nearest and before October 19, 2024, midnight Eastern time, regardless of subject matter.
3. The one email in your chief FOIA officer's sent email folder or equivalent which was sent nearest and before October 19, 2024, midnight Eastern time, regardless of subject matter.
4. The total full-time equivalent count of people who work for your FOIA office as of October 19, 2024.

This request is expressly limited to Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco, Firearms and Explosives's own FOIA office. Please do not refer it to any other agency or division. This request is expressly not a Privacy Act request, and no PA waiver will be provided.

Please provide the email records in EML, Maildir, MBOX, MIX, MSG, or PST format only — not PDF, Word, image, etc — including all metadata (e.g. full email headers as received/sent) and attachments, without alteration other than narrowly tailored electronic redaction of specifically claimed exemptions that do not affect any part of non exempt information (and, in particular, without rasterization).

Please provide the fourth record as a statement in your response letter, or at your option, as the most readily available record, in original electronic format as currently stored on your computer systems, which includes that information.

Please provide all records either as individual files, or as an unencrypted ZIP file, uploaded to MuckRock. Do not apply any encryption, DRM, or other restriction.

I request fee waiver, because
* Fiat Fiendum is a 501(c)(3) non-profit;
* this request is for public interest, non-commercial purposes;
* these records would give a snapshot of insight into the everyday processes of FOIA offices; and
* these records are being requested in order to conduct a government-wide audit of agencies' FOIA compliance.

In the event that you deny fee waiver, please process this request as-is, because I will not agree to any fees.

Please be sure to provide:
* 5 USC 552(a)(6)(A)(i)(II) FOIA Public Liaison information
* 5 USC 552(a)(6)(A)(i)(III)(aa) appeal information
* 5 USC 552(a)(6)(A)(i)(III)(bb) OGIS information
* 5 USC 552(a)(7)(A) tracking number
* 5 USC 552(a)(7)(B)(ii) completion ETA

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,
Sai
President, Fiat Fiendum, Inc.

P.S. Sai is my full legal name.

communications.subject: Washington Public Records Act Request: Email Metadata (Hollingsworth)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Washington Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

The following metadata for emails sent/received by all accounts operated by CM Hollingsworth's office between the dates of May 21, 2025 - May 25, 2025:
- Sender
- Recipient (To, CC, BCC)
- Date and time sent
- Subject

As this is a request for metadata, please do not include the email body in the returned records.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Rose Terse

The records being made available to you at this time include the records that you requested. 
To download your records, please: 
 
  * Navigate to the Public Records Request Center. 
  * Select 'My Records Request Center'. 
  * Select 'View My Requests'. You may be asked to login. 
  * Select this request: C226867-052525. 
  * Select the 'View Files' button. 
  * You can download records individually or all at the same time by clicking 'Download All'. 
  *  Please save your records as you may only download them from the system three times. If you do not download your records within 30 days of request closure, the link to your records will expire. 
If you believe you have received privileged or confidential records in error, please notify the City of Seattle immediately, through the Public Records Request Center or by email. Privileged or confidential records provided or received in error should not be reviewed, used, disseminated, distributed, or copied, and should be destroyed immediately. Thank you in advance for your cooperation. 
We have not prepared a detailed exemption log, as only limited information has been redacted from the responsive records. The information normally provided in an exemption log, such as title, author, recipient, subject, and number of pages, is readily ascertainable from looking at the redacted records. Redactions have been applied throughout the documents pursuant to the following exemption:   
 Ex. 01A Attorney-Client            Privileged Communications - RCW 42.56.070 and 5.60.060 Records reflect            communication between a client and an attorney for the purpose of seeking or            providing legal advice. 
The Legislative Department has now provided all responsive records. We consider your request closed and plan to take no further action to fulfill this request. If you have any follow-up questions or would like to initiate an administrative appeal under MDAR 17-0002 Section 6, please contact us within 10 business days after downloading your records, after which this request will no longer be monitored for communications. You may also seek judicial review of our response to your request for a period of one year, beginning as of the date of this message, consistent with RCW 42.56.550. 
Sincerely, 
Matthew C. Jaeger 
(206) 684-8159 
Legislative Department

communications.subject: Florida Sunshine Law Request: Public Records Request - Stanley Williams
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Florida Sunshine Law, I hereby request the following records:

Requesting all available body-worn camera footage, dashcam or in-car video, booking and transport footage (if available), and the full arrest report related to the December 9, 2023 arrest of Stanley Williams in Columbia County, Florida. Around midnight, Williams stole an ambulance while experiencing an altered mental state and led deputies on a pursuit that ended when he drove the vehicle onto the front lawn of the Columbia County Sheriff’s Office operations center. Williams was taken into custody without incident and later hospitalized. He was charged with grand theft and fleeing and eluding.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days.

Sincerely,

Behind The Badge

communications.subject: California Public Records Act Request: Asset Forfeiture Funds (Fontana Police Department)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the California Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

- Any accounting records or statistics on seized real estate, vehicles, firearms, funds in bank accounts, and seizures made by the department, as well as seizures made by federal authorities where the department receives a share under the MOUs the department has in place with numerous agencies describing how assets are to be divided.

- Records and data that outlines what was purchased using money from the fund, including dates, descriptions, and total spent. 

- Any annual reports produced civil asset forfeiture program.

- Documents showing the balance of any funds currently in the department Civil Asset Forfeiture fund.

-A list of all items seized through civil asset forfeiture and retained for use by the department

- Sales of non-monetary assets, receipts of sale for vehicles, or the destruction of other non-monetary assets

-Please also include any information relating to contested seizures. This request does not include court documents for individual forfeiture cases.
 
The period for this request is for the last 10 years.

Preferably released in .CSV form when possible

title: ALPR Audit (St. Charles Department Of Public Works)

communications.subject: The Missouri Sunshine Law Request: ALPR Audit (St. Charles Department Of Public Works)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the The Missouri Sunshine Law, I hereby request the following records:

1. Organization Audit in Flock.
The report should include data logged from the period January 1, 2025, to the date this request is processed. Per Flock's documentation, the Organization Audit is available within the Insights tab and is defined as searches done within the agency.

2. Network Audit in Flock.
The report should include data logged from the period of January 1, 2025, to the date this request is processed. Per Flock's documentation, the Network Audit is available within the Insights tab and is defined as searches of the organization’s Flock network by any agency in the Flock System.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 3 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Scott Kampas

communications.subject: Saint Charles Police Department - Police Record Request PD2025-382: Confirmation
communications.communication:
Dear Requestor, 
  
 The St. Charles City Police Department Records Division received your open records request pursuant to Missouri's Sunshine Law, Chapter 610, RSMo on Wednesday, June 4, 2025.  
  
 Your request reference number is Request Number: PD2025-382  
 Your security key is 94DB11EF  
  
 Please have both reference numbers available when communicating with our staff regarding your request.  
  
 Three Business Day Notice Requirement: 
The requested records are not immediately available for dissemination or inspection. This department is required to notify you that additional research time will be required to fulfill the request. This correspondence satisfies the Sunshine Law's notice requirement within the required three-business-day period. § 610.023.3, RSMo. 
 
Estimated Time for Completion: 
The majority of our requests are fulfilled within seven business days. Some requests require additional research time due to their scope or complexity. We will conduct an initial review of your request. If we estimate that the request will be fulfilled within seven business days, we will not send an updated time estimate. However, if we estimate that the request will take longer than seven business days, we will provide an updated time estimate that provides a detailed justification for the additional research time. 
 
Billing: 
This department will charge fees for copies and research time required for fulfilling records requests at the actual cost of research time. § 610.026, RSMo. The Missouri Supreme Court recently determined that "staff time is the time required to provide access to public records maintained on computer facilities, recording tapes or disks, videotapes or films, pictures, maps, slides, graphics, illustrations or similar audio or visual items." Gross v. Parson, 624 S.W.3d 877, 884-89 (Mo. 2021) (internal quotations omitted). You will only be charged for copies and staff research time as permitted by Missouri law. 
 
Our team will forward a bill estimate to your attention once we have calculated the permissible costs and fees. This department will not provide the responsive records until receipt of payment. § 610.026.2, RSMo. 
 
We appreciate your patience as we review, research, and fulfill your open records request. 
  
 Thank you,  
  
 Saint Charles Police Department 
1781 Zumbehl Road
Saint Charles, MO 63303 
(636) 940-4619

communications.subject: RE: California Public Records Act Request #543
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

I'm following up on the following California Public Records Act request, copied below, and originally submitted on May 17, 2024. You had previously indicated that it would be completed on Dec. 2, 2024. I wanted to check on the status of my request, and to see if there was a new estimated completion date.  You had assigned it reference number #543.

Thanks for your help, and let me know if further clarification is needed.

communications.subject: Massachusetts Public Records Law Request: Chelsea SRO MOU
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Massachusetts Public Records Law, G.L. c.66, §10, I hereby request a copy of the most recent Memorandum of Understanding (MoU) between Chelsea Public Schools and Chelsea Police department on behalf of Citizens for Juvenile Justice, a non-profit advocating for equitable youth justice in MA.  

I am specifically seeking records that detail the collaboration between Chelsea Public Schools and Chelsea Police Department regarding school resource officers (SROs) and their responsibilities in Chelsea Public Schools.  

I request that any fees be waived, as the requested information is in public interest. However, if fees are unavoidable, I would appreciate if you would inform me before fulfilling my request. I would also prefer if the request could be filled electronically via email.  

Thank you for considering my request, I look forward to hearing back within 10 business days.    

Sincerely,

Joshua Dankoff
Director of Strategic Initiatives, Citizens for Juvenile Justice

communications.subject: Freedom of Information Act Request: Larry Flint
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

A copy of all documents, FBI files, audio recordings, and electronic communications pertaining to Larry Flint, Born November 1, 1942, Lakeville, KY, Died February 10, 2021, Hollywood Hills, Los Angeles, CA

Attached to this request is an obituary for Larry Flint published in the New York Times on Feb 10, 2021.

As a member of the news media and a contributor to outlets like The New Republic, The Intercept, and The Nation, I request that any associated fees be waved.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Daniel Boguslaw

communications.subject: Florida Sunshine Law Request: Records Managment Manual (Tallahassee Police Department)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Florida Sunshine Law, I hereby request the following records:

The manual for the records management system (RMS) that the department uses to record data on police incidents, traffic stops, field stops, and any other relevant police activity.  Including the data dictionary, glossary of terms, record layout, user guide, and any other records that describe the database(s). As well as the instruction manual, or any other type of guide, distributed to law enforcement personnel dictating how they should use the database(s).

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days.

Sincerely,

Sam

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Oklahoma Open Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

Any and all public records related to Incident #04-51703, including initial offense reports, arrest records, jail registers, radio logs, crime summaries, and e-mail communications, as well as evidence inventory logs, property room general reports and collection forms, chain of custody forms, arrest reports, crime/incident reports and logs, and search warrants/affidavits.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days.

Sincerely,

Kimberly Shainfeld

communications.subject: RE: Oklahoma Open Records Act Request #OCPD-3750-2025
communications.communication:
To whom it may concern: 
I am writing to formally appeal the denial of my request for records under the Oklahoma Open Records Act (“ORA”), which I submitted on 3/26/25. I respectfully request a written explanation detailing the specific grounds for the denial, including the precise subsections of the ORA that are being relied upon.
According to the ORA, “all records of public bodies and public officials shall be open to any person for inspection, copying, or mechanical reproduction during regular business hours…” unless specifically exempted by law. Your response cited the Oklahoma Open Records Act generally, referring to Sections 2, 5, 8, 14, and 20, but did not indicate what specific subsections within those provisions justify withholding the records I requested.
To ensure that the denial complies with the legal requirements of the ORA, and to allow me to properly evaluate the legitimacy of the denial, I ask that you provide the following:
The specific subsection(s) within ORA Sections 2, 5, 8, 14, and/or 20 that are being relied upon.


1. A description of how those subsections apply to the records I requested.


2. A list or description of the categories of records being withheld in whole or in part.


3. Whether any portion of the requested records is non-exempt and therefore subject to partial disclosure with redactions, as required by Oklahoma law.


The law is clear: ORA emphasizes transparency and access to public records as a matter of public policy. The Act requires that denials be specific and justified under the law; vague or categorical denials are inconsistent with both the letter and spirit of the Act.
I respectfully request a response to this appeal within a reasonable timeframe, ideally within seven (7) business days of receipt, so that I may determine my next steps.
If you require any clarification regarding my original request or this appeal, please let me know promptly.
Thank you.

communications.subject: Re: RE: Oklahoma Open Records Act Request #OCPD-3750-2025
communications.communication:
Good Day, 
  
 RE: OCPD-3750-2025 / 2004-0051703 
  
 Per the Municipal Counselors Office on Apr. 2, 2025 @ 06:25 AM: "2004-0051703 provide open record version of incident report 000 and arrest report 013. Otherwise denied; ORA Sections 8 and 14." 
  
 After being unsure that your materials had been mailed out, I mailed out another copy of your materials on 05/27/2025. 
  
 In order to file an appeal: 
  
 The process is defined in Section 8 of the Open Records Act Law Enforcement Agency Records Available for Public Inspection, a link provided on the JustFOIA web page under “Open Records.” 
  
 Otherwise, the original decision was made by the Municipal Counselors Office. They can be contacted at 405-297-3830. Contact name is Orval Jones. Please provide your request number, OCPD-3750-2025, when you call so that they can reference your request. 
  
 Thank you.

communications.subject: RE: Oklahoma Open Records Act Request #OCPD-4095-2025
communications.communication:
To whom it may concern: 
I am writing to formally appeal the denial of my request for records under the Oklahoma Open Records Act (“ORA”), which I submitted on 3/26/25. I respectfully request a written explanation detailing the specific grounds for the denial, including the precise subsections of the ORA that are being relied upon.
According to the ORA, “all records of public bodies and public officials shall be open to any person for inspection, copying, or mechanical reproduction during regular business hours…” unless specifically exempted by law. Your response cited the Oklahoma Open Records Act generally, referring to Sections 2, 5, 8, 14, and 20, but did not indicate what specific subsections within those provisions justify withholding the records I requested.
To ensure that the denial complies with the legal requirements of the ORA, and to allow me to properly evaluate the legitimacy of the denial, I ask that you provide the following:
The specific subsection(s) within ORA Sections 2, 5, 8, 14, and/or 20 that are being relied upon.


1. A description of how those subsections apply to the records I requested.


2. A list or description of the categories of records being withheld in whole or in part.


3. Whether any portion of the requested records is non-exempt and therefore subject to partial disclosure with redactions, as required by Oklahoma law.


The law is clear: ORA emphasizes transparency and access to public records as a matter of public policy. The Act requires that denials be specific and justified under the law; vague or categorical denials are inconsistent with both the letter and spirit of the Act.
I respectfully request a response to this appeal within a reasonable timeframe, ideally within seven (7) business days of receipt, so that I may determine my next steps.
If you require any clarification regarding my original request or this appeal, please let me know promptly.
Thank you.

I also request that, if appropriate, fees be waived as I believe this request is in the public interest. communications.subject: RE: New York Freedom of Information Law Request: New York SEA response
communications.communication:
Dear Ms. Garnand:

This is to acknowledge receipt of your Freedom of Information Law (FOIL) request for State Education Department (SED) records regarding New York SEA response.  The reference number for this request is FL-FL-25/543.   Please be advised that you will hear further from the Department by approximately June 5, 2025 as to whether your request will be granted or denied in whole or in part.

SED charges the statutorily permitted fees under FOIL. These include $.25 per page for photocopies or the actual cost of reproducing records requested under FOIL (Public Officers Law §87[1][b][iii]). Payment must be made to the NYS Education Department by check or money order. Do not send any payment until you are notified that your request is granted and informed of the charge for your request. If your request is granted, the records will be provided to you in the manner requested (i.e. hardcopy or electronic), or if not specified, in a reasonable manner selected by this office.

If your request is granted, and there is a fee, one of the following will happen:

1. If your request can be filled immediately, and the total photocopy or reproduction fee is under $25.00, staff will forward the requested records to you with a statement what you owe. Or:

2. If the reproduction fee or photocopy fee for your request is $25.00 or more, you will be advised of the page count (+100 pages) or other expenses and the fee(s) owed in advance of our providing the records. Upon receipt of payment, staff will photocopy or otherwise reproduce the requested records and transmit, as appropriate. Or:

3. If it will take time to locate and/or photocopy or otherwise reproduce the records you have requested, you will be given a date by which you will be provided with a page count and/or estimated cost to fulfil your request.

Please note, there is no provision in law or regulation requiring the waiver of a fee under FOIL.
Regards,
Records Access Officer

communications.subject: Freedom of Information Act Request: CENTCOM Iraq Coup/Uprising
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

1) Any and all intelligence reports or analyses concerning the possibility of a military coup or popular uprising in Iraq prepared between April 1, 2002 and April 1, 2003.

2) Any and all contingency plans for responding to a military coup or popular uprising in Iraq prepared between April 1, 2002 and April 1, 2003.

3) Any and all intelligence analyses concerning the morale or cohesion of the Iraqi armed forces prepared between January 1, 2003 and April 1, 2003.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

David Lindsey

communications.subject: Wisconsin Open Records Act Request: Pandemic Unemployment Fraud Wisconsin Investigation
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Wisconsin Open Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

Subject: Freedom of Information Request for Unemployment Fraud Investigation Records

Dear Records Custodian,

I am submitting this Freedom of Information request under the Wisconsin Open Records Law (Wis. Stat. §§ 19.31–19.39) to obtain records related to an unemployment fraud investigation conducted by the Wisconsin Department of Workforce Development (DWD), specifically involving Adjudicator #5139 (Mark, last name withheld) and Investigator Christine Francke.

I am seeking the following records:





The current status of the unemployment fraud investigation referenced in communications with Christine Francke on February 21, 2025, and May 16, 2025.



Copies of correspondence notes, internal memos, or reports generated by or involving Adjudicator #5139 (Mark) and Christine Francke related to the investigation, including any notes from a phone call on or about February 20, 2025, with Alexander Lennon regarding evidence collection.



Records acknowledging or referencing the receipt and review of evidence I submitted, including:





Documents emailed on February 21, 2025, detailing bicycle sales and Venmo transactions for the period referenced in the investigation.



Evidence submitted on May 16, 2025, including the IPV Hearing Decision (EXHIBIT D 2024-12-20), redacted BMO account statements, US Bank account proof, E-Trade account details, a forensic accountant’s tally of deposits (Tanya BMO Working_01March2024.xlsx), a letter of engagement from Anish Neupane, a memo from private investigator Jeff Janda, and related correspondence.



A police report (EXHIBIT B 2025-05-13 WPD Report 2025-124662 wFollowUp) emailed on May 21, 2025, confirming the individual’s self-identification in connection with the IPV report and PUA fraud investigation.



Any correspondence between DWD staff (including Christine Francke or Adjudicator #5139) and the individual under investigation, Angie Dempewolfe, regarding the PUA fraud or IPV FoodShare fraud investigation, to the extent permitted by law.



Any determinations, findings, or decisions related to the PUA overpayment or fraud allegations, redacted as necessary to comply with confidentiality requirements.

I understand that certain records may be subject to confidentiality restrictions under state or federal law, including those protecting personal information or ongoing investigations. I request that any non-exempt portions of the records be released, with appropriate redactions applied to comply with privacy laws. If any records are withheld, please provide a written explanation citing the specific statutory exemptions.

To facilitate processing, my contact information is: Alexander Lennon Email: alennon727@gmail.com Phone: 608-214-6492

Please confirm receipt of this request and provide an estimated timeline for response. If there are any fees associated with this request, please notify me in advance. I prefer to receive the records electronically via email, if possible.

Thank you for your attention to this matter.

Sincerely, Alexander Lennon

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days.

Sincerely,

Alexander Lennon

communications.communication:
Good afternoon,

This email is in response to your May 29, 2025 public records request for the following records:

"I am submitting this Freedom of Information request under the Wisconsin Open Records Law (Wis. Stat. §§ 19.31–19.39) to obtain records related to an unemployment fraud investigation conducted by the Wisconsin Department of Workforce Development (DWD), specifically involving Adjudicator #5139 (Mark, last name withheld) and Investigator Christine Francke.

I am seeking the following records:

The current status of the unemployment fraud investigation referenced in communications with Christine Francke on February 21, 2025, and May 16, 2025.

Copies of correspondence notes, internal memos, or reports generated by or involving
Adjudicator #5139 (Mark) and Christine Francke related to the investigation, including any notes from a phone call on or about February 20, 2025, with Alexander Lennon regarding evidence collection.

Records acknowledging or referencing the receipt and review of evidence I submitted, including:

Documents emailed on February 21, 2025, detailing bicycle sales and Venmo transactions for the period referenced in the investigation.

Evidence submitted on May 16, 2025, including the IPV Hearing Decision (EXHIBIT D 2024-12-20), redacted BMO account statements, US Bank account proof, E-Trade account details, a forensic accountant’s tally of deposits (Tanya BMO Working_01March2024.xlsx), a letter of engagement from Anish Neupane, a memo from private investigator Jeff Janda, and related correspondence.

A police report (EXHIBIT B 2025-05-13 WPD Report 2025-124662 wFollowUp) emailed on May 21, 2025, confirming the individual’s self-identification in connection with the IPV report and PUA fraud investigation.

Any correspondence between DWD staff (including Christine Francke or Adjudicator #5139) and the individual under investigation, Angie Dempewolfe, regarding the PUA fraud or IPV FoodShare fraud investigation, to the extent permitted by law.

Any determinations, findings, or decisions related to the PUA overpayment or fraud allegations, redacted as necessary to comply with confidentiality requirements."

For the item of your request requesting "Records acknowledging or referencing the receipt and review of evidence I submitted," the responsive records have been attached to this message. Please note that the Department would have normally redacted your personal email address from these records. However, since you are the individual who submitted this personally identifiable information when you submitted the information to the Department's Unemployment Insurance Division, these records are being provided without redaction.

For the remaining items of your request:

Information Identifying Individual Unemployment Insurance Claimants: The Department considers information regarding whether an individual is receiving, has received, or has applied for unemployment insurance to be confidential. See 20 CFR §§ 603.4, 603.5; Wis. Stat. § 108.14(7)(a); and Wis. Admin. Code § DWD 149.02. Therefore, the Department has withheld documents that identify individuals who are receiving, have received, or have applied for unemployment insurance.

Pursuant to Wis. Stat. § 19.35(4)(b), to the extent this is a denial, this determination is subject to review by mandamus under Wis. Stat. § 19.37(1) or upon application to a district attorney or the Attorney General.

Thank you,

Open Records
State of Wisconsin | Department of Workforce Development
OpenRecords@dwd.wisconsin.gov<mailto:OpenRecords@dwd.wisconsin.gov>
